      • onClickSave

        public void onClickSave(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        RUNTIME ERROR Runtime error that occurred was an invocation target exception kept being thrown. Could not figure out the problem until I realized when calling updatePart() that the id of the part did not match the index. Part id was = 1 and index was = 0. Solved by creating an index variable and passing that into the update part instead of having Part Ids begin from 0.
        Parameters:
        actionEvent - event user clicks save after modifying a part
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - from the FXMLLLoader

        public void initialize(java.net.URL location,
